replies.comment info:
@nancy martinez 
Thank you, Nancy, for your comment.
Yes! Belarus shares a large border with Ukraine, yet few Ukrainians sought refuge in Belarus. It is important to research the recent history regarding the relations between these neighboring countries, especially those who do not receive a lot of media attention.

@Karissa 
Thank you, Karissa.
You ask a great question… due to the large count of refugees during this month, how does this devastation of violence and war compare to other moments in history during the past century? Further, is the "proportion" of Ukrainian citizens seeking refuge compared to their total population stronger than what other countries experienced in the graph?

@Maggie S 
You offered a “hopeful” question, Maggie.
I would also be interested to know how many refugees from Venezuela returned to their home country after the devastation from 4-5 years ago. Has Venezuela been able to rebuild during the past 5 years, and at what pace? Can the progress in Venezuela be any indication of what can be expected from the Ukrainians in the years to come?

@Vanessa 
Thank you for your comments, Vanessa.
See today’s posting of the Reveal! The additional graphs will help answer your question from part 2.

@Nomas 
Thank you for your comment, Nomas.
Venezuela experienced extreme devastation 5 years ago. Why did their citizens not experience the same global attention as Ukraine? What was unique regarding Venezuela’s conflict compared to what we are witnessing today with Ukraine?

@Caroline C. 
Thank you for the comment, Caroline.
Not only has the Ukrainian refugee “count” exceeded the Venezuela count, but the Ukrainians’ “rate” of refugees leaving the country far exceeds any other country represented in the graph. It would be interesting to know the proportion of refugees to total population for the each of the respective countries. Some countries have a smaller refugee count, but also a smaller population when compared to other countries.

@Abby 
Thank you, Abby, for your comments.
Yes! The timeline is important. The number of Ukrainian refugees during the past month (now) surpasses the next highest number of refugees from Venezuela. However, are the proportion of refugees from the other countries higher than Ukraine’s based on their respective total populations?

@Faith 
